<xar:comment>
    Initialise the jquery.linktracker tool.
    Based on http://www.glennjones.net/Post/811/AjaxLinkTracker22Thedownload.htm
</xar:comment>

<xar:comment>Make sure jQuery is going to be loaded.</xar:comment>
<xar:template file="jquery" module="jquery" />

<xar:comment>Load the main javascript.</xar:comment>
<xar:base-include-javascript filename="jquery.linktracker.js" module="jquery" />

<xar:comment>
    Initialise the main javascript.
    There are no options to pass in yet, but the destination tracker script would
    be a good one.
</xar:comment>
<xar:base-include-javascript type="code" code="jQuery(document).ready(function(){jQuery().linktracker('');});" />
